actions.comment:
Thanks for the detailed report, and to @themcoo for the excellent investigation!

**Root cause:** This is a bug in Skia's native PNG codec when handling indexed (palette-based) PNG images. The upstream fix is at [google/skia commit 983ae8625b](https://github.com/google/skia/commit/983ae8625b05737e7528fac074030d11e225961d), and a PR (mono/skia#98) was opened to bring this into SkiaSharp's Skia fork.

**Workaround (available now):** Convert the bitmap color type to `Rgba8888` before encoding to bypass the buggy indexed codec path:

```csharp
using (SKBitmap indexed = SKBitmap.Decode("sourceImage.png"))
{
    using var converted = indexed.Copy(SKColorType.Rgba8888);
    using var fs = new FileStream("destImage.png", FileMode.Create);
    converted.Encode(fs, SKEncodedImageFormat.Png, 100);
}
```

We'll investigate whether this fix was included in SkiaSharp 3.x (via a Skia milestone update) or still needs to be merged.
